# Agape — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` for local dev or to `.env.production` for the
# GitHub Actions deploy. Each variable is documented below with the
# rationale, owner of the credential, and what to do at handoff.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudflare Web Analytics — the first Cloudflare third-party script
#   (DESIGN.md §6.2.3 — cookieless, no consent banner required).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where to find: Cloudflare dashboard → your agapenj.org zone → Analytics.
# Owner of record: the client.
# Post-handoff: the client pastes their own token here OR in the
# GitHub Actions secret `PUBLIC_CF_ANALYTICS_TOKEN`.
# If unset: the Cloudflare beacon is omitted from <head>. The build
# never fails because of an unset analytics token.
PUBLIC_CF_ANALYTICS_TOKEN=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Web3Forms — contact form endpoint
#   (DESIGN.md §3.4 + §6.6 — Web3Forms recommended, Formspree alt).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where to find: https://web3forms.com — generate an access key, point
# it at info@agapenj.org. The free tier is sufficient; no Web3Forms
# account is required at runtime — only the access key + email routing.
#
# RECIPIENT EMAIL (configured in Web3Forms dashboard, NOT in form data):
#   Web3Forms delivers form submissions to the email address set in the
#   dashboard for this access key. For Agape, the recipient is:
#     → info@agapenj.org
#   The client must verify this in the Web3Forms dashboard before the
#   demo; submissions will silently fail or be mis-routed if the
#   dashboard email doesn't match.
#
# SENDER ENVELOPE (DESIGN.md §6.2.3): the notification is sent FROM
#   noreply@agapenj.org (also configured in the Web3Forms dashboard).
#   This is the §6.2.3 envelope posture — recipients see a no-reply
#   sender so they reply to info@agapenj.org directly, not to Web3Forms.
#
# Owner of record: the client.
# Post-handoff: the client regenerates the key in Web3Forms if/when
# they want to rotate it. The form endpoint (https://api.web3forms.com/submit)
# is hard-coded in the ContactForm component — only this key changes.
PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudflare Turnstile — invisible captcha
#   (DESIGN.md §6.6 — spam protection alongside honeypot field).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where to find: Cloudflare dashboard → Turnstile → add site → pick
# "Invisible" widget mode. Two keys: a site key (PUBLIC) and a secret
# key (PRIVATE, server-side only — used by the Web3Forms endpoint).
# Owner of record: the client.
# Post-handoff: both keys stay in the Web3Forms dashboard; only the
# site key is referenced here. If unset: the form still works, but
# spam protection falls back to the honeypot field only.
PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=